---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Data Processing Agreement | AUXO Data Labs"
  description="Data Processing Agreement (DPA) for AUXO Data Labs' data analytics consultancy services in compliance with UAE PDPL and GDPR."
>
  <div class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <LegalLayout
        title="Data Processing Agreement (DPA)"
        lastUpdated="January 15, 2025"
        effectiveDate="January 1, 2025"
        summary="This Data Processing Agreement governs how AUXO Data Labs processes personal data on behalf of our clients. It ensures compliance with UAE PDPL, GDPR, and international data protection standards for all data analytics consultancy services."
      >
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          This Data Processing Agreement ("DPA") forms part of the service agreement between AUXO Data Labs ("Processor") and the Client ("Controller") for the provision of data analytics services.
        </p>
        <p>
          This DPA sets out the terms on which AUXO Data Labs processes personal data on behalf of the Client.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Definitions</h2>
        <p>In this DPA:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>"Personal Data"</strong> means any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person</li>
          <li><strong>"Processing"</strong> means any operation performed on personal data</li>
          <li><strong>"Controller"</strong> means the Client who determines the purposes and means of processing</li>
          <li><strong>"Processor"</strong> means AUXO Data Labs who processes personal data on behalf of the Controller</li>
          <li><strong>"Data Protection Laws"</strong> means applicable data protection legislation including UAE PDPL and GDPR where applicable</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Scope and Purpose of Processing</h2>
        <h3>3.1 Subject Matter</h3>
        <p>
          The Processor shall process personal data as necessary to provide data analytics services as described in the main service agreement.
        </p>

        <h3>3.2 Nature and Purpose</h3>
        <p>
          Processing will involve analysis, storage, and transformation of personal data for the purposes of providing business intelligence, data analytics, and related services.
        </p>

        <h3>3.3 Types of Personal Data</h3>
        <p>The types of personal data processed may include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Customer data (names, contact details, transaction history)</li>
          <li>Employee data (if applicable to the analytics scope)</li>
          <li>User behavior data and analytics identifiers</li>
          <li>Any other data categories as specified in the service agreement</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Processor Obligations</h2>
        <h3>4.1 Processing Instructions</h3>
        <p>
          The Processor shall process personal data only on documented instructions from the Controller, unless required to do so by applicable law.
        </p>

        <h3>4.2 Confidentiality</h3>
        <p>
          The Processor shall ensure that persons authorized to process personal data have committed themselves to confidentiality or are under an appropriate statutory obligation of confidentiality.
        </p>

        <h3>4.3 Security Measures</h3>
        <p>
          The Processor shall implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure a level of security appropriate to the risk, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Encryption of personal data in transit and at rest</li>
          <li>Regular security assessments and penetration testing</li>
          <li>Access controls and authentication mechanisms</li>
          <li>Regular backups and disaster recovery procedures</li>
          <li>Employee training on data security and privacy</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.4 Sub-Processors</h3>
        <p>
          The Processor may engage sub-processors with the Controller's prior written consent.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Processor shall impose the same data protection obligations on sub-processors through written contracts.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Data Subject Rights</h2>
        <p>
          The Processor shall assist the Controller in responding to requests from data subjects to exercise their rights under Data Protection Laws, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Right of access</li>
          <li>Right to rectification</li>
          <li>Right to erasure</li>
          <li>Right to restriction of processing</li>
          <li>Right to data portability</li>
          <li>Right to object</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Data Breach Notification</h2>
        <p>
          The Processor shall notify the Controller without undue delay (and in any event within 48 hours) upon becoming aware of a personal data breach.
        </p>
        <p>
          The notification shall include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Description of the nature of the breach</li>
          <li>Categories and approximate number of data subjects affected</li>
          <li>Likely consequences of the breach</li>
          <li>Measures taken or proposed to address the breach</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Any transfer of personal data outside the UAE shall be conducted in accordance with Data Protection Laws and with appropriate safeguards in place, such as:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Standard contractual clauses</li>
          <li>Adequacy decisions</li>
          <li>Binding corporate rules</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Audit Rights</h2>
        <p>
          The Processor shall make available to the Controller all information necessary to demonstrate compliance with this DPA and allow for audits and inspections upon reasonable notice.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Data Deletion and Return</h2>
        <p>
          Upon termination of services, the Processor shall, at the Controller's choice, delete or return all personal data and delete existing copies, unless retention is required by law.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Liability and Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          Each party shall be liable for damages caused by its processing of personal data in violation of Data Protection Laws.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Processor shall indemnify the Controller against claims arising from the Processor's breach of this DPA.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Duration and Termination</h2>
        <p>
          This DPA shall remain in effect for the duration of the service agreement and shall terminate upon completion of all processing activities or earlier termination of the service agreement.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          This DPA shall be governed by the laws of the United Arab Emirates and Data Protection Laws applicable to the processing activities.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Contact for Data Protection Matters</h2>
        <p>
          For questions regarding data processing and this DPA, please contact:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: privacy@auxodata.ae</li>
          <li>Address: As specified in the main service agreement</li>
        </ul>
      </LegalLayout>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
